\end{gathered}
$$

(b) From Equation ($\begin{aligned} V_C & =\frac{3 a^2 c \sqrt{3}}{2}\end{aligned}$), for HCP the unit cell volume for is

$$
V{C}=\frac{3 a^{2} c \sqrt{3}}{2}
$$

since, for $\mathrm{Ti}, c=1.58 a$, then

$$
V{C}=\frac{3(1.58) a^{3} \sqrt{3}}{2}=1.058 \times 10^{-22} \mathrm{~cm}^{3} / \text { unit cell }
$$

Now, solving for $a$

$$
