$$

Substituting these values in Eq. $F_z = V \chi_{\text{mag}} H \frac{dB}{dz}$  and solving for $\chi_{\text {mag }}$, one obtains

$$
\chi_{\text {mag }}=\frac{4.9 \times 10^{-7}}{2 \times 10^{-6} \times 9000 \times 1}=2.7 \times 10^{-5}
$$

Given that $R=0.04$, applying Eq. $R = \frac{(n - 1)^2 + \kappa^2}{(n + 1)^2 + \kappa^2}$ and ignoring $\kappa$ yields $n=1.5$. To calculate $\alpha_{a}$, use is made of Eq. $T = \frac{I_{\text{out}}}{I_0} = \frac{(1 - R)^2 e^{-\alpha_{\text{a}} x}}{1 - R^2 e^{-2\alpha_{\text{a}} x}}$. However, given that the loss is small, the second term in the denominator can be neglected, and Eq. (16.19) simplifies to

$$
\begin{aligned}
T & =(1-R)^{2} e^{-\alpha_{a} x} \\
0.8 & =(1-0.04)^{2} e^{-\alpha_{a}(0.001)}
